        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/philips-kept-warnings-about-dangerous-cpaps-secret-profits-soared">
                                    Philips Kept Complaints About Dangerous Breathing Machines Secret While Company Profits Soared
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            Tainted CPAP machines and ventilators went to children, the elderly and at least 700,000 veterans despite internal warnings. Company insiders said the devices posed an “unacceptable” risk.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/debbie-cenziper">Debbie Cenziper</a>, ProPublica; <span class="name">Michael D. Sallah</span>, <span class="name">Michael Korsh</span> and <span class="name">Evan Robinson-Johnson</span>, <a href="http://www.post-gazette.com/">Pittsburgh Post-Gazette</a>;  and <span class="name">Monica Sager</span>, Northwestern University,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2023-09-27EDT06:00">Sept. 27, 6 a.m. EDT</time>
        </p>

            </div>
</div>
                            </div>
            </ol> <!-- end .most-read-group -->

</div> <!-- end .most-read -->



    
